SLEEP(1)                         User Commands                        SLEEP(1)

NAME
       sleep - delay for a specified amount of time

SYNOPSIS
       sleep NUMBER[SUFFIX]...
       sleep OPTION

DESCRIPTION
       Pause for NUMBER seconds.  SUFFIX may be 's' for seconds (the
       default), 'm' for minutes, 'h' for hours, or 'd' for days.
       NUMBER may be a floating-point number.

       Given two or more arguments, pause for the amount of time
       specified by the sum of their values.

OPTIONS
       --help display this help and exit

       --version
              output version information and exit

EXAMPLES
       sleep 5        sleep for 5 seconds
       sleep 1.5      sleep for 1.5 seconds
       sleep 2m       sleep for 2 minutes
       sleep 1h 30m   sleep for 1 hour and 30 minutes

EXIT STATUS
       0      if OK

       1      if errors occurred

